lemma hasLaw_Z (a : α) (m : ℕ) :
  HasLaw (fun ω ↦ ω.2 m a) (ν a) (P.prod (Bandit.streamMeasure ν)) where
  map_eq := by
    calc (P.prod (Bandit.streamMeasure ν)).map (fun ω ↦ ω.2 m a)
    _ = ((P.prod (Bandit.streamMeasure ν)).snd).map (fun ω ↦ ω m a) := by
      rw [Measure.snd, Measure.map_map (by fun_prop) (by fun_prop)]
      rfl
    _ = (Bandit.streamMeasure ν).map (fun ω ↦ ω m a) := by simp
    _ = ((Measure.infinitePi fun _ ↦ Measure.infinitePi ν).map (fun ω ↦ ω m)).map
        (fun ω ↦ ω a) := by
      rw [Bandit.streamMeasure, Measure.map_map (by fun_prop) (by fun_prop)]
      rfl
    _ = ν a := by simp_rw [(measurePreserving_eval_infinitePi _ _).map_eq]
```

This lemma is establishing that the law of `Z m a` (the `m`-th component of the trajectory `ω` for action `a`) is `ν a`. This is a standard property in a Markov environment, where the distribution of the `m`-th state is given by the `m`-fold composition of the transition kernel `ν`.

